\pard\plain\s0\qj\widctlpar\f0\fs24\sl240\slmult1 \sb60 \fi0 Given a finite set <<:$A$:>>, denote <<:$\\#A$:>> as the cardinality of a set <<:$A$:>>, and denote <<:$\\Delta A$:>> as the set of probability distribution over <<:$A$:>>. \par
\pard\plain\s0\qj\widctlpar\f0\fs24\sl240\slmult1 \fi360 The square bracket <<:$[]$:>> after a quantifier <<:$\\exists, \\forall$:>> will be read as \ldblquote {\i such that}\rdblquote . For instance, <<:$\\exists a \\in A [c\\in A, c=a]$:>> will be read as \ldblquote exists <<:$a$:>> in <<:$A$:>> such that <<:$c$:>> in A and <<:$c$:>> is equal to <<:$a$:>>.\rdblquote  . \par
