\pard\plain\s0\qj\widctlpar\f0\fs24\sl240\slmult1 \sb60 \fi0 There are <<:$n$:>> players. Denote <<:$N=\\\{1,2,...,n\\\}$:>> as the set of players. We say <<:$G$:>> is a network if <<:$G$:>> is a point-to-set function mapping from <<:$N$:>> to a subset of <<:$N$:>> containing <<:$i\\in N$:>>. Moreover, we denote <<:$G_i=G(i)$:>> as <<:$i$:>>\rquote s neighbors and also denote <<:$\\bar\{G\}_i=G_i\\backslash \\\{i\\\}$:>> as <<:$i$:>>\rquote s neighborhood excluding <<:$i$:>> self. We say <<:$G$:>> is fixed if <<:$G$:>> is not random, and say <<:$G$:>> is undirected if for all <<:$i,j$:>> if <<:$j\\in G_i$:>> then <<:$i\\in G_j$:>>. Throughout this paper, I assume <<:$G$:>> is finite, fixed, commonly known, and undirected. For all player <<:$i$:>>, let <<:$\\Theta_i=\\\{Rebel,Inert\\\}$:>> and denote <<:$\\theta_i\\in \\Theta_i$:>> as an element in <<:$\\Theta_i$:>>. The set of states of nature is <<:$\\Theta=\\prod_\{j\\in N\}\\Theta_j$:>> and let <<:$\\theta\\in \\Theta$:>> is a state of nature. For convenience, denote <<:$[Rebels](\\theta)=\\\{j:\\theta_j=Rebel\\\}$:>> be the set of Rebels given <<:$\\theta$:>>, and let <<:$\\Theta_\{G_i\}=\\prod_\{j\\in G_i\}\\Theta_j$:>> and <<:$\\theta_\{G_i\}\\in \\Theta_\{G_i\}$:>>. Let <<:$p_\{G_i\}:\\Theta \\rightarrow 2^\{\\Theta\}$:>> be <<:$i$:>>\rquote s information partition function such that <<:$p_\{G_i\}(\\theta)=\\\{\\theta_\{G_i\}\\\}\\times \\prod_\{j\\not\\in G_i\}\\Theta_j$:>>, and let <<:$\\mathcal\{P\}_\{G_i\}=\\\{p_\{G_i\}(\\theta)\\\}_\{\\theta\\in \\Theta\}$:>> be <<:$i$:>>\rquote s information sets about <<:$\\theta$:>>. That is, whenever nature chooses a state, <<:$i$:>> knows his own <<:$\\theta_i$:>> and his neighbor <<:$j$:>>\rquote s <<:$\\theta_j$:>>. \par
\pard\plain\s0\qj\widctlpar\f0\fs24\sl240\slmult1 \fi360 There is a game, <<:$k$:>>-threshold game, infinitely repeated played with common discounted factor <<:$\\delta$:>> in a fixed <<:$G$:>>. Time is discrete, infinite horizontal. At the beginning of this game, a state is realized and there is a common prior <<:$\\pi\\in \\Delta \\Theta$:>> over <<:$\\Theta$:>>. After a state is realized, players simultaneously choose an action <<:$a_\{\\theta_i\}\\in A_\{\\theta_i\}$:>> in each period afterwards. If <<:$\\theta_i=Rebel$:>>, then <<:$A_\{\\theta_i\}=\\\{\\textbf\{revolt\}, \\textbf\{stay\}\\\}$:>>. If <<:$\\theta_i=Inert$:>>, then <<:$A_\{\\theta_i\}=\\\{\\textbf\{stay\}\\\}$:>>. Let <<:$a_\{\\theta_i\}\\in A_\{\\theta_i\}$:>> be <<:$i$:>>\rquote s action if <<:$i$:>>\rquote s type is <<:$\\theta_i$:>>, and let <<:$a_\{-\\theta_i\}\\in \\Pi_\{j\\in N,j\\neq i\}A_\{\\theta_j\}$:>> be the actions taken by players other than <<:$i$:>>. Player <<:$i$:>>\rquote s static pay-off function, denoted as <<:$u_\{\\theta_i\}: \\Pi_\{j\\in N\}A_\{\\theta_j\}\\rightarrow \\mathbb\{R\}$:>>, in this <<:$k$:>>-threshold game is defined as followings. {\par
