}\pard\plain\s0\qj\widctlpar\f0\fs24\sl240\slmult1 \sb60 \fi0 The goal of this paper is to show that a (weak) sequential APEX equilibrium always exists when <<:$k<n$:>> in FFCCU networks without cycle given that <<:$\\delta$:>> is sufficiently high. I define cycles in FFCCU networks in the following definition and state my main theorem in Theorem \~{\field{\*\fldinst{\lang1024 REF BMthm_main_result \\* MERGEFORMAT }}{\fldrslt{2}}}. {\par
