\pard\plain\s0\qj\widctlpar\f0\fs24\sl240\slmult1 \fi360 In the equilibrium path, two phases, {\i reporting period} and {\i coordination period}, occur in turns finitely in the following way, <<:\\[\\underbrace\{<\\text\{coordination period\}>\}_\{0-block\}\\underbrace\{<\\text\{reporting period\}><\\text\{coordination period\}>\}_\{1-block\}...\\]:>> I.e. after nature chooses a state, all the Rebels start with <<:$0$:>>-block, then enter to <<:$1$:>>-block,...,and so on. <<:$0$:>>-block has only one period, coordination period. The <<:$t$:>>-blocks, <<:$t\\geq 1$:>> has two periods, reporting period and coordination period, where reporting period occurs first and then coordination period follows. The length of each period in each block is finite but endogenous.\par
\pard\plain\s0\qj\widctlpar\f0\fs24\sl240\slmult1 \fi360 If a sequence of actions has been played in reporting period ({\i resp.} coordination period), I called it a {\i reporting messages} ({\i resp.} {\i coordination messages}). In reporting period in each <<:$t$:>>-block (<<:$t\\geq 1$:>>), Rebels use the sequences defined in Table \~{\field{\*\fldinst{\lang1024 REF BMTable_msg_reporting \\* MERGEFORMAT }}{\fldrslt{2}}} to report their <<:$I^\{t-1\}_i$:>> contingent on the histories they observed. In coordination period in each <<:$t$:>>-block (<<:$t\\geq 0$:>>), Rebels use the sequences defined in Table \~{\field{\*\fldinst{\lang1024 REF BMTable_msg_coordination \\* MERGEFORMAT }}{\fldrslt{4}}} to check if there are some Rebels have known the relevant information. After the coordination period in each <<:$t$:>>-block (<<:$t\\geq 0$:>>), they either start to coordination to some actions or enter to next reporting period in <<:$t+1$:>>-block. I start to give the details of these messages.\par
